      <p class="step-label">Step 3 of 9</p>
      <h1>Recruit Team Members</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Build your team with passionate members from different skill backgrounds.</p>
      <section class="content-section">
        <p>A strong FTC team usually needs a mix of builders, coders, designers, and leaders. Start by finding students who are excited to learn and willing to show up consistently.</p>
        <div class="content-subsection">
          <h3>Good recruiting targets</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Students interested in programming, CAD, or electrical work</li>
            <li>People who enjoy public speaking, writing, or organizing</li>
            <li>Members from art, business, and media backgrounds who can support outreach</li>
            <li>Younger students who can grow into the team over time</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Action:</strong> Ask teachers, club leaders, and classmates to help spread the word, then hold a short interest meeting to explain the team mission.</p>
      </section>
      <div class="step-actions">
        <a href="/start-team-step4" class="btn btn-primary">Next: Find a Coach / Mentor →</a>
      </div>
